[{"text": "So, I've known a lot of fish in my life.", "start": 16.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "I've loved only two.", "start": 20.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That first one,", "start": 23.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it was more like a passionate affair.", "start": 25.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It was a beautiful fish:", "start": 28.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "flavorful, textured, meaty,", "start": 30.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a bestseller on the menu.", "start": 33.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What a fish.", "start": 35.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 37.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Even better,", "start": 40.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it was farm-raised to the supposed highest standards", "start": 42.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of sustainability.", "start": 45.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So you could feel good about selling it.", "start": 48.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I was in a relationship with this beauty", "start": 52.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for several months.", "start": 54.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "One day, the head of the company called", "start": 58.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and asked if I'd speak at an event", "start": 60.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about the farm's sustainability.", "start": 62.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"Absolutely,\" I said.", "start": 64.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Here was a company trying to solve", "start": 66.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "what's become this unimaginable problem for us chefs:", "start": 69.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "How do we keep fish on our menus?", "start": 73.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "For the past 50 years,", "start": 77.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "we've been fishing the seas", "start": 80.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "like we clear-cut forests.", "start": 82.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's hard to overstate the destruction.", "start": 85.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Ninety percent of large fish, the ones we love --", "start": 90.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the tunas, the halibuts, the salmons, swordfish --", "start": 93.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "they've collapsed.", "start": 96.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "There's almost nothing left.", "start": 98.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So, for better or for worse,", "start": 101.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "aquaculture, fish farming, is going to be a part of our future.", "start": 104.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "A lot of arguments against it:", "start": 107.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Fish farms pollute -- most of them do anyway --", "start": 109.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and they're inefficient. Take tuna,", "start": 112.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a major drawback.", "start": 114.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's got a feed conversion ratio", "start": 116.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of 15 to one.", "start": 118.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "That means it takes fifteen pounds of wild fish", "start": 120.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to get you one pound of farm tuna.", "start": 122.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Not very sustainable.", "start": 126.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It doesn't taste very good either.", "start": 128.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So here, finally,", "start": 131.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "was a company trying to do it right.", "start": 133.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I wanted to support them.", "start": 135.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The day before the event,", "start": 138.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I called the head of P.R. for the company.", "start": 140.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Let's call him Don.", "start": 143.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "\"Don,\" I said, \"just to get the facts straight, you guys are famous", "start": 147.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "for farming so far out to sea, you don't pollute.\"", "start": 150.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "\"That's right,\" he said. \"We're so far out,", "start": 153.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the waste from our fish gets distributed,", "start": 156.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "not concentrated.\"", "start": 159.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And then he added,", "start": 161.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"We're basically a world unto ourselves.", "start": 163.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That feed conversion ratio? 2.5 to one,\" he said.", "start": 167.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "\"Best in the business.\"", "start": 170.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "2.5 to one, great.", "start": 172.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"2.5 what? What are you feeding?\"", "start": 174.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"Sustainable proteins,\" he said.", "start": 176.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "\"Great,\" I said. Got off the phone.", "start": 179.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And that night, I was lying in bed, and I thought:", "start": 182.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "What the hell is a sustainable protein?", "start": 185.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 187.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "So the next day, just before the event, I called Don.", "start": 192.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I said, \"Don, what are some examples of sustainable proteins?\"", "start": 194.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "He said he didn't know. He would ask around.", "start": 198.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Well, I got on the phone with a few people in the company;", "start": 201.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "no one could give me a straight answer", "start": 203.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "until finally, I got on the phone", "start": 206.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with the head biologist.", "start": 209.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Let's call him Don too.", "start": 211.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 213.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "\"Don,\" I said,", "start": 217.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"what are some examples of sustainable proteins?\"", "start": 219.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Well, he mentioned some algaes", "start": 222.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and some fish meals,", "start": 224.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and then he said chicken pellets.", "start": 226.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I said, \"Chicken pellets?\"", "start": 228.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He said, \"Yeah, feathers, skin,", "start": 230.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "bone meal, scraps,", "start": 232.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "dried and processed into feed.\"", "start": 234.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I said, \"What percentage", "start": 237.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of your feed is chicken?\"", "start": 239.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Thinking, you know, two percent.", "start": 242.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "\"Well, it's about 30 percent,\" he said.", "start": 245.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I said, \"Don, what's sustainable", "start": 248.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "about feeding chicken to fish?\"", "start": 251.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 253.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "There was a long pause on the line,", "start": 258.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and he said, \"There's just too much chicken in the world.\"", "start": 261.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 264.26, "duration": 6.0}, {"text": "I fell out of love with this fish.", "start": 270.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 272.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "No, not because I'm some self-righteous,", "start": 274.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "goody-two shoes foodie.", "start": 277.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I actually am.", "start": 279.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 281.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "No, I actually fell out of love with this fish because, I swear to God,", "start": 283.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "after that conversation, the fish tasted like chicken.", "start": 285.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 288.26, "duration": 10.0}, {"text": "This second fish,", "start": 298.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "it's a different kind of love story.", "start": 301.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's the romantic kind,", "start": 304.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the kind where the more you get to know your fish,", "start": 307.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "you love the fish.", "start": 310.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I first ate it at a restaurant", "start": 313.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in southern Spain.", "start": 315.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "A journalist friend had been talking about this fish for a long time.", "start": 317.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "She kind of set us up.", "start": 320.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 322.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It came to the table", "start": 324.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a bright, almost shimmering, white color.", "start": 326.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The chef had overcooked it.", "start": 331.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Like twice over.", "start": 334.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Amazingly, it was still delicious.", "start": 337.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Who can make a fish taste good", "start": 340.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "after it's been overcooked?", "start": 344.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I can't,", "start": 346.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but this guy can.", "start": 348.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Let's call him Miguel --", "start": 350.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "actually his name is Miguel.", "start": 352.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 354.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And no, he didn't cook the fish, and he's not a chef,", "start": 357.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "at least in the way that you and I understand it.", "start": 359.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "He's a biologist", "start": 363.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "at Veta La Palma.", "start": 365.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's a fish farm in the southwestern corner of Spain.", "start": 367.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's at the tip of the Guadalquivir river.", "start": 370.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Until the 1980s,", "start": 373.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the farm was in the hands of the Argentinians.", "start": 375.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They raised beef cattle", "start": 378.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on what was essentially wetlands.", "start": 380.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They did it by draining the land.", "start": 383.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They built this intricate series of canals,", "start": 385.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and they pushed water off the land and out into the river.", "start": 388.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Well, they couldn't make it work,", "start": 392.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "not economically.", "start": 394.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And ecologically, it was a disaster.", "start": 396.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It killed like 90 percent of the birds,", "start": 399.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which, for this place, is a lot of birds.", "start": 401.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And so in 1982,", "start": 404.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a Spanish company with an environmental conscience", "start": 406.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "purchased the land.", "start": 408.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What did they do?", "start": 410.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They reversed the flow of water.", "start": 412.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They literally flipped the switch.", "start": 414.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Instead of pushing water out,", "start": 416.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they used the channels to pull water back in.", "start": 418.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They flooded the canals.", "start": 420.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They created a 27,000-acre fish farm --", "start": 422.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "bass, mullet,", "start": 426.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "shrimp, eel --", "start": 428.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and in the process, Miguel and this company", "start": 431.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "completely reversed the ecological destruction.", "start": 434.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The farm's incredible.", "start": 438.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I mean, you've never seen anything like this.", "start": 440.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "You stare out at a horizon", "start": 443.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that is a million miles away,", "start": 446.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and all you see are flooded canals", "start": 448.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and this thick, rich marshland.", "start": 450.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I was there not long ago with Miguel.", "start": 455.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "He's an amazing guy,", "start": 458.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "like three parts Charles Darwin and one part Crocodile Dundee.", "start": 461.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 464.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Okay? There we are slogging through the wetlands,", "start": 466.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and I'm panting and sweating, got mud up to my knees,", "start": 470.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and Miguel's calmly conducting a biology lecture.", "start": 472.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Here, he's pointing out a rare Black-shouldered Kite.", "start": 476.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Now, he's mentioning the mineral needs of phytoplankton.", "start": 479.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And here, here he sees a grouping pattern", "start": 483.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that reminds him of the Tanzanian Giraffe.", "start": 486.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It turns out, Miguel spent the better part of his career", "start": 491.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in the Mikumi National Park in Africa.", "start": 494.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I asked him how he became", "start": 497.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "such an expert on fish.", "start": 499.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He said, \"Fish? I didn't know anything about fish.", "start": 501.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I'm an expert in relationships.\"", "start": 504.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And then he's off, launching into more talk", "start": 507.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about rare birds and algaes", "start": 509.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and strange aquatic plants.", "start": 511.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And don't get me wrong, that was really fascinating, you know,", "start": 513.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the biotic community unplugged, kind of thing.", "start": 516.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's great, but I was in love.", "start": 519.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And my head was swooning over that", "start": 522.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "overcooked piece of delicious fish I had the night before.", "start": 525.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So I interrupted him. I said,", "start": 528.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"Miguel, what makes your fish taste so good?\"", "start": 530.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He pointed at the algae.", "start": 532.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"I know, dude, the algae, the phytoplankton,", "start": 534.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the relationships: It's amazing.", "start": 537.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But what are your fish eating?", "start": 540.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What's the feed conversion ratio?\"", "start": 542.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Well, he goes on to tell me", "start": 545.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "it's such a rich system", "start": 549.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that the fish are eating what they'd be eating in the wild.", "start": 551.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The plant biomass, the phytoplankton,", "start": 554.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the zooplankton, it's what feeds the fish.", "start": 557.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The system is so healthy,", "start": 559.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it's totally self-renewing.", "start": 561.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "There is no feed.", "start": 563.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Ever heard of a farm that doesn't feed its animals?", "start": 566.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Later that day, I was driving around this property with Miguel,", "start": 573.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and I asked him, I said, \"For a place that seems so natural,", "start": 575.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "unlike like any farm I'd ever been at,", "start": 579.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "how do you measure success?\"", "start": 584.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "At that moment, it was as if", "start": 587.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a film director called for a set change.", "start": 590.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And we rounded the corner", "start": 592.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and saw the most amazing sight:", "start": 594.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "thousands and thousands of pink flamingos,", "start": 596.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a literal pink carpet for as far as you could see.", "start": 599.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "\"That's success,\" he said.", "start": 603.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"Look at their bellies, pink.", "start": 606.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They're feasting.\"", "start": 608.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Feasting? I was totally confused.", "start": 610.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I said, \"Miguel, aren't they feasting on your fish?\"", "start": 612.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 614.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"Yes,\" he said.", "start": 616.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 618.26, "duration": 6.0}, {"text": "\"We lose 20 percent of our fish", "start": 624.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and fish eggs to birds.", "start": 626.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Well, last year, this property", "start": 630.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "had 600,000 birds on it,", "start": 632.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "more than 250 different species.", "start": 634.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's become, today, the largest", "start": 636.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and one of the most important", "start": 639.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "private bird sanctuaries in all of Europe.\"", "start": 642.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "I said, \"Miguel, isn't a thriving bird population", "start": 646.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "like the last thing you want on a fish farm?\"", "start": 649.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 651.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He shook his head, no.", "start": 653.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He said, \"We farm extensively,", "start": 655.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "not intensively.", "start": 658.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is an ecological network.", "start": 661.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The flamingos eat the shrimp.", "start": 664.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The shrimp eat the phytoplankton.", "start": 666.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So the pinker the belly,", "start": 668.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the better the system.\"", "start": 670.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Okay, so let's review:", "start": 673.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a farm that doesn't feed its animals,", "start": 675.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and a farm that measures its success", "start": 678.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "on the health of its predators.", "start": 681.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "A fish farm, but also a bird sanctuary.", "start": 683.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Oh, and by the way, those flamingos,", "start": 686.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they shouldn't even be there in the first place.", "start": 688.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They brood in a town", "start": 690.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "150 miles away,", "start": 692.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "where the soil conditions", "start": 694.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are better for building nests.", "start": 696.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Every morning, they fly", "start": 698.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "150 miles into the farm.", "start": 700.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And every evening, they fly 150 miles back.", "start": 704.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 707.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "They do that because they're able to follow", "start": 714.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the broken white line", "start": 717.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of highway A92.", "start": 719.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 721.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "No kidding.", "start": 723.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I was imagining a \"March of the Penguins\" thing,", "start": 725.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "so I looked at Miguel.", "start": 728.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I said, \"Miguel, do they fly", "start": 730.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "150 miles to the farm,", "start": 732.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and then do they fly", "start": 734.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "150 miles back at night?", "start": 736.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Do they do that for the children?\"", "start": 738.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "He looked at me like I had just quoted a Whitney Houston song.", "start": 741.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 744.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "He said, \"No; they do it because the food's better.\"", "start": 748.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 751.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I didn't mention the skin of my beloved fish,", "start": 753.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "which was delicious -- and I don't like fish skin;", "start": 761.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I don't like it seared, I don't like it crispy.", "start": 763.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's that acrid, tar-like flavor.", "start": 766.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I almost never cook with it.", "start": 770.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Yet, when I tasted it at that restaurant in southern Spain,", "start": 773.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "it tasted not at all like fish skin.", "start": 776.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It tasted sweet and clean,", "start": 779.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "like you were taking a bite of the ocean.", "start": 782.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I mentioned that to Miguel, and he nodded.", "start": 785.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "He said, \"The skin acts like a sponge.", "start": 787.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's the last defense before anything enters the body.", "start": 789.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It evolved to soak up impurities.\"", "start": 792.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And then he added,", "start": 794.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"But our water has no impurities.\"", "start": 796.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "OK. A farm that doesn't feed its fish,", "start": 802.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a farm that measures its success", "start": 806.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "by the success of its predators.", "start": 809.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And then I realized when he says,", "start": 811.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"A farm that has no impurities,\"", "start": 813.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "he made a big understatement,", "start": 816.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because the water that flows through that farm", "start": 818.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "comes in from the Guadalquivir River.", "start": 820.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's a river that carries with it", "start": 823.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "all the things that rivers tend to carry these days:", "start": 825.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "chemical contaminants,", "start": 828.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "pesticide runoff.", "start": 830.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And when it works its way through the system", "start": 832.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and leaves,", "start": 835.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the water is cleaner than when it entered.", "start": 837.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The system is so healthy, it purifies the water.", "start": 839.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So, not just a farm that doesn't feed its animals,", "start": 843.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "not just a farm that measures its success", "start": 845.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "by the health of its predators,", "start": 848.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but a farm that's literally a water purification plant --", "start": 850.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and not just for those fish,", "start": 856.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but for you and me as well.", "start": 859.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Because when that water leaves, it dumps out into the Atlantic.", "start": 861.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "A drop in the ocean, I know,", "start": 866.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but I'll take it, and so should you,", "start": 868.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "because this love story,", "start": 871.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "however romantic,", "start": 875.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is also instructive.", "start": 877.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "You might say it's a recipe", "start": 879.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for the future of good food,", "start": 881.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "whether we're talking about bass or beef cattle.", "start": 883.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "What we need now is", "start": 887.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a radically new conception of agriculture,", "start": 889.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "one in which the food actually tastes good.", "start": 892.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Laughter)", "start": 894.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 896.26, "duration": 6.0}, {"text": "But for a lot people,", "start": 902.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that's a bit too radical.", "start": 904.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We're not realists, us foodies;", "start": 907.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we're lovers.", "start": 909.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We love farmers' markets,", "start": 911.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we love small family farms,", "start": 913.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "we talk about local food,", "start": 916.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we eat organic.", "start": 918.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And when you suggest these are the things", "start": 921.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that will ensure the future of good food,", "start": 923.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "someone, somewhere stands up and says,", "start": 927.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"Hey guy, I love pink flamingos,", "start": 929.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "but how are you going to feed the world?\"", "start": 933.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "How are you going to feed the world?", "start": 936.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Can I be honest?", "start": 939.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I don't love that question.", "start": 941.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "No, not because we already produce", "start": 944.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "enough calories to more than feed the world.", "start": 946.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "One billion people will go hungry today.", "start": 949.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "One billion -- that's more than ever before --", "start": 952.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "because of gross inequalities in distribution,", "start": 956.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "not tonnage.", "start": 959.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Now, I don't love this question because it's determined the logic", "start": 962.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of our food system for the last 50 years.", "start": 964.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Feed grain to herbivores,", "start": 967.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "pesticides to monocultures, chemicals to soil,", "start": 970.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "chicken to fish,", "start": 972.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and all along agribusiness", "start": 975.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "has simply asked,", "start": 978.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"If we're feeding more people more cheaply,", "start": 980.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "how terrible could that be?\"", "start": 982.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That's been the motivation,", "start": 985.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it's been the justification:", "start": 987.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it's been the business plan", "start": 989.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of American agriculture.", "start": 992.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We should call it what it is:", "start": 994.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a business in liquidation,", "start": 996.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a business that's quickly eroding", "start": 999.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "ecological capital that makes that very production possible.", "start": 1002.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That's not a business,", "start": 1005.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and it isn't agriculture.", "start": 1007.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Our breadbasket is threatened today,", "start": 1009.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "not because of diminishing supply,", "start": 1012.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but because of diminishing resources.", "start": 1014.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Not by the latest combine and tractor invention,", "start": 1017.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but by fertile land;", "start": 1020.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "not by pumps, but by fresh water;", "start": 1022.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "not by chainsaws, but by forests;", "start": 1025.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and not by fishing boats and nets, but by fish in the sea.", "start": 1028.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Want to feed the world?", "start": 1031.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Let's start by asking: How are we going to feed ourselves?", "start": 1033.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Or better: How can we create conditions", "start": 1037.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that enable every community", "start": 1040.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to feed itself?", "start": 1043.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 1045.26, "duration": 7.0}, {"text": "To do that,", "start": 1052.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "don't look at the agribusiness model for the future.", "start": 1054.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's really old, and it's tired.", "start": 1057.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's high on capital, chemistry and machines,", "start": 1059.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "and it's never produced anything really good to eat.", "start": 1063.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Instead, let's look to the ecological model.", "start": 1068.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "That's the one that relies on two billion years", "start": 1072.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of on-the-job experience.", "start": 1075.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Look to Miguel,", "start": 1078.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "farmers like Miguel.", "start": 1080.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Farms that aren't worlds unto themselves;", "start": 1082.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "farms that restore instead of deplete;", "start": 1085.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "farms that farm extensively", "start": 1090.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "instead of just intensively;", "start": 1092.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "farmers that are not just producers,", "start": 1094.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but experts in relationships.", "start": 1097.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Because they're the ones", "start": 1099.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that are experts in flavor, too.", "start": 1101.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And if I'm going to be really honest,", "start": 1104.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they're a better chef than I'll ever be.", "start": 1106.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "You know, I'm okay with that,", "start": 1109.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "because if that's the future of good food, it's going to be delicious.", "start": 1112.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 1115.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 1117.26, "duration": 17.0}]